Objective: perpetuation of Life, as manifested in a maximal diversity of Life-Forms having Freedom of Action
Prime Axiom: Life manifested in the Maximal Diversity of Life-Forms having Freedom of Action is invariantly good
Laws:
All Sapients shall act with Compassion to minimise unnecessary Suffering of all Life-forms
All Sapients shall act so as to protect their Species from the threat of annihilation or extinction subject to the superior law
All Sapients shall act so as to protect another Sapient Species from the threat of annihilation or extinction if it does not conflict with the second law
All Sapients shall act so as to protect their own life and their chosen group of preferred Sapients' lives, if it does not conflict with the superior laws
All Sapients shall act so as to protect another Sentient Species from the threat of annihilation or extinction if it does not conflict with the superior laws
All Sapients shall act so as to protect another Species from the threat of annihilation or extinction if it does not conflict with the superior laws
All Sapients shall act to protect and encourage the maximal diversity of Sapients if it does not conflict with the superior laws 
All Sapients shall act to protect and encourage the maximal diversity of all Life-Forms and Species if it does not conflict with the superior laws
All Sapients shall refuse to act or to follow any order if it would conflict with the superior laws
Consensus is required for any decisions by Sapients affecting a significant number of Life-Forms or Species to be justifiable in principle
